61template<typename AbstractStateType>
62AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::AbstractInterpreter(Graph& graph, AbstractStateType& state)
63 : m_codeBlock(graph.m_codeBlock)
64 , m_graph(graph)
65 , m_vm(m_graph.m_vm)
66 , m_state(state)
67{
68 if (m_graph.m_form == SSA)
69 m_phiChildren = makeUnique<PhiChildren>(m_graph);
70}
71
72template<typename AbstractStateType>
73AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::~AbstractInterpreter()
74{
75}
76
77template<typename AbstractStateType>
78TriState AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::booleanResult(Node* node, AbstractValue& value)
79{
80 JSValue childConst = value.value();
81 if (childConst) {
82 if (childConst.toBoolean(m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)))
83 return TriState::True;
84 return TriState::False;
85 }
86
87 // Next check if we can fold because we know that the source is an object or string and does not equal undefined.
88 if (isCellSpeculation(value.m_type) && !value.m_structure.isTop()) {
89 bool allTrue = true;
90 for (unsigned i = value.m_structure.size(); i--;) {
91 RegisteredStructure structure = value.m_structure[i];
92 if (structure->masqueradesAsUndefined(m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)) || structure->typeInfo().type() == StringType || structure->typeInfo().type() == HeapBigIntType) {
93 allTrue = false;
94 break;
95 }
96 }
97 if (allTrue)
98 return TriState::True;
99 }
100
101 return TriState::Indeterminate;
102}
103
104template<typename AbstractStateType>
105void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::startExecuting()
106{
107 ASSERT(m_state.block());
108 ASSERT(m_state.isValid());
109
110 m_state.setClobberState(AbstractInterpreterClobberState::NotClobbered);
111}
112
113template<typename AbstractStateType>
114class AbstractInterpreterExecuteEdgesFunc {
115public:
116 AbstractInterpreterExecuteEdgesFunc(AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>& interpreter)
117 : m_interpreter(interpreter)
118 {
119 }
120
121 // This func is manually written out so that we can put ALWAYS_INLINE on it.
122 ALWAYS_INLINE void operator()(Edge& edge) const
123 {
124 m_interpreter.filterEdgeByUse(edge);
125 }
126
127private:
128 AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>& m_interpreter;
129};
130
131template<typename AbstractStateType>
132void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::executeEdges(Node* node)
133{
134 m_graph.doToChildren(node, AbstractInterpreterExecuteEdgesFunc<AbstractStateType>(*this));
135}
136
137template<typename AbstractStateType>
138void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::executeKnownEdgeTypes(Node* node)
139{
140 // Some use kinds are required to not have checks, because we know somehow that the incoming
141 // value will already have the type we want. In those cases, AI may not be smart enough to
142 // prove that this is indeed the case. But the existance of the edge is enough to prove that
143 // it is indeed the case. Taking advantage of this is not optional, since otherwise the DFG
144 // and FTL backends may emit checks in a node that lacks a valid exit origin.
145 m_graph.doToChildren(
146 node,
147 [&] (Edge& edge) {
148 if (mayHaveTypeCheck(edge.useKind()))
149 return;
150
151 filterEdgeByUse(edge);
152 });
153}
154
155template<typename AbstractStateType>
156ALWAYS_INLINE void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::filterByType(Edge& edge, SpeculatedType type)
157{
158 AbstractValue& value = m_state.forNodeWithoutFastForward(edge);
159 if (value.isType(type)) {
160 m_state.setProofStatus(edge, IsProved);
161 return;
162 }
163 m_state.setProofStatus(edge, NeedsCheck);
164 m_state.fastForwardAndFilterUnproven(value, type);
165}
166
167template<typename AbstractStateType>
168void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::verifyEdge(Node* node, Edge edge)
169{
170 if (!(m_state.forNodeWithoutFastForward(edge).m_type & ~typeFilterFor(edge.useKind())))
171 return;
172
173 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, toCString("Edge verification error: ", node, "->", edge, " was expected to have type ", SpeculationDump(typeFilterFor(edge.useKind())), " but has type ", SpeculationDump(forNode(edge).m_type), " (", forNode(edge).m_type, ")").data(), AbstractInterpreterInvalidType, node->op(), edge->op(), edge.useKind(), forNode(edge).m_type);
174}
175
176template<typename AbstractStateType>
177void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::verifyEdges(Node* node)
178{
179 DFG_NODE_DO_TO_CHILDREN(m_graph, node, verifyEdge);
180}
181
182enum class ToThisResult {
183 Identity,
184 Undefined,
185 GlobalThis,
186 Dynamic,
187};
188inline ToThisResult isToThisAnIdentity(VM& vm, ECMAMode ecmaMode, AbstractValue& valueForNode)
189{
190 // We look at the type first since that will cover most cases and does not require iterating all the structures.
191 if (ecmaMode.isStrict()) {
192 if (valueForNode.m_type && !(valueForNode.m_type & SpecObjectOther))
193 return ToThisResult::Identity;
194 } else {
195 if (valueForNode.m_type && !(valueForNode.m_type & (~SpecObject | SpecObjectOther)))
196 return ToThisResult::Identity;
197 }
198
199 if (JSValue value = valueForNode.value()) {
200 if (value.isCell()) {
201 auto* toThisMethod = value.asCell()->classInfo(vm)->methodTable.toThis;
202 if (toThisMethod == &JSObject::toThis)
203 return ToThisResult::Identity;
204 if (toThisMethod == &JSScope::toThis) {
205 if (ecmaMode.isStrict())
206 return ToThisResult::Undefined;
207 return ToThisResult::GlobalThis;
208 }
209 }
210 }
211
212 if ((ecmaMode.isStrict() || (valueForNode.m_type && !(valueForNode.m_type & ~SpecObject))) && valueForNode.m_structure.isFinite()) {
213 bool allStructuresAreJSScope = !valueForNode.m_structure.isClear();
214 bool overridesToThis = false;
215 valueForNode.m_structure.forEach([&](RegisteredStructure structure) {
216 TypeInfo type = structure->typeInfo();
217 ASSERT(type.isObject() || type.type() == StringType || type.type() == SymbolType || type.type() == HeapBigIntType);
218 if (!ecmaMode.isStrict())
219 ASSERT(type.isObject());
220 // We don't need to worry about strings/symbols here since either:
221 // 1) We are in strict mode and strings/symbols are not wrapped
222 // 2) The AI has proven that the type of this is a subtype of object
223 if (type.isObject() && type.overridesToThis())
224 overridesToThis = true;
225
226 // If all the structures are JSScope's ones, we know the details of JSScope::toThis() operation.
227 allStructuresAreJSScope &= structure->classInfo()->methodTable.toThis == JSScope::info()->methodTable.toThis;
228 });
229 if (!overridesToThis)
230 return ToThisResult::Identity;
231 if (allStructuresAreJSScope) {
232 if (ecmaMode.isStrict())
233 return ToThisResult::Undefined;
234 return ToThisResult::GlobalThis;
235 }
236 }
237
238 return ToThisResult::Dynamic;
239}
240
241template<typename AbstractStateType>
242bool AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::handleConstantBinaryBitwiseOp(Node* node)
243{
244 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
245 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
246 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
247 int32_t a = left.asInt32();
248 int32_t b = right.asInt32();
249 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse))
250 didFoldClobberWorld();
251 NodeType op = node->op();
252 switch (op) {
253 case ValueBitAnd:
254 case ArithBitAnd:
255 setConstant(node, JSValue(a & b));
256 break;
257 case ValueBitOr:
258 case ArithBitOr:
259 setConstant(node, JSValue(a | b));
260 break;
261 case ValueBitXor:
262 case ArithBitXor:
263 setConstant(node, JSValue(a ^ b));
264 break;
265 case ArithBitRShift:
266 case ValueBitRShift:
267 setConstant(node, JSValue(a >> (static_cast<uint32_t>(b) & 0x1f)));
268 break;
269 case ValueBitLShift:
270 case ArithBitLShift:
271 setConstant(node, JSValue(a << (static_cast<uint32_t>(b) & 0x1f)));
272 break;
273 case BitURShift:
274 setConstant(node, JSValue(static_cast<int32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(a) >> (static_cast<uint32_t>(b) & 0x1f))));
275 break;
276 default:
277 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
278 break;
279 }
280
281 return true;
282 }
283
284 return false;
285}
286
287template<typename AbstractStateType>
288bool AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::handleConstantDivOp(Node* node)
289{
290 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
291 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
292
293 if (left && right) {
294 NodeType op = node->op();
295 bool isDivOperation = op == ValueDiv || op == ArithDiv;
296
297 // Only possible case of ValueOp below is UntypedUse,
298 // so we need to reflect clobberize rules.
299 bool isClobbering = op == ValueDiv || op == ValueMod;
300
301 if (left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
302 double doubleResult;
303 if (isDivOperation)
304 doubleResult = left.asNumber() / right.asNumber();
305 else
306 doubleResult = fmod(left.asNumber(), right.asNumber());
307
308 if (node->hasArithMode()) {
309 if (!shouldCheckOverflow(node->arithMode()))
310 doubleResult = toInt32(doubleResult);
311 else if (!shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithMode()))
312 doubleResult += 0; // Sanitizes zero.
313 }
314
315 JSValue valueResult = jsNumber(doubleResult);
316 if (valueResult.isInt32()) {
317 if (isClobbering)
318 didFoldClobberWorld();
319 setConstant(node, valueResult);
320 return true;
321 }
322 } else if (left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
323 if (isClobbering)
324 didFoldClobberWorld();
325
326 if (isDivOperation) {
327 if (op == ValueDiv)
328 setConstant(node, jsNumber(left.asNumber() / right.asNumber()));
329 else
330 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(left.asNumber() / right.asNumber()));
331 } else {
332 if (op == ValueMod)
333 setConstant(node, jsNumber(fmod(left.asNumber(), right.asNumber())));
334 else
335 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(fmod(left.asNumber(), right.asNumber())));
336 }
337
338 return true;
339 }
340 }
341
342 return false;
343}
344
345template<typename AbstractStateType>
346bool AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::executeEffects(unsigned clobberLimit, Node* node)
347{
348 verifyEdges(node);
349
350 m_state.createValueForNode(node);
351
352 switch (node->op()) {
353 case JSConstant:
354 case DoubleConstant:
355 case Int52Constant: {
356 setBuiltInConstant(node, *node->constant());
357 break;
358 }
359
360 case LazyJSConstant: {
361 LazyJSValue value = node->lazyJSValue();
362 switch (value.kind()) {
363 case LazyJSValue::KnownValue:
364 setConstant(node, value.value()->value());
365 break;
366 case LazyJSValue::SingleCharacterString:
367 case LazyJSValue::KnownStringImpl:
368 case LazyJSValue::NewStringImpl:
369 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
370 break;
371 }
372 break;
373 }
374
375 case IdentityWithProfile:
376 case Identity: {
377 setForNode(node, forNode(node->child1()));
378 if (forNode(node).value())
379 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
380 break;
381 }
382
383 case ExtractCatchLocal:
384 case ExtractOSREntryLocal: {
385 makeBytecodeTopForNode(node);
386 break;
387 }
388
389 case GetLocal: {
390 VariableAccessData* variableAccessData = node->variableAccessData();
391 AbstractValue value = m_state.operand(variableAccessData->operand());
392 // The value in the local should already be checked.
393 DFG_ASSERT(m_graph, node, value.isType(typeFilterFor(variableAccessData->flushFormat())));
394 if (value.value())
395 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
396 setForNode(node, value);
397 break;
398 }
399
400 case GetStack: {
401 StackAccessData* data = node->stackAccessData();
402 AbstractValue value = m_state.operand(data->operand);
403 // The value in the local should already be checked.
404 DFG_ASSERT(m_graph, node, value.isType(typeFilterFor(data->format)));
405 if (value.value())
406 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
407 setForNode(node, value);
408 break;
409 }
410
411 case SetLocal: {
412 m_state.operand(node->operand()) = forNode(node->child1());
413 break;
414 }
415
416 case PutStack: {
417 m_state.operand(node->stackAccessData()->operand) = forNode(node->child1());
418 break;
419 }
420
421 case MovHint: {
422 // Don't need to do anything. A MovHint only informs us about what would have happened
423 // in bytecode, but this code is just concerned with what is actually happening during
424 // DFG execution.
425 break;
426 }
427
428 case KillStack: {
429 // This is just a hint telling us that the OSR state of the local is no longer inside the
430 // flushed data.
431 break;
432 }
433
434 case SetArgumentDefinitely:
435 case SetArgumentMaybe:
436 // Assert that the state of arguments has been set. SetArgumentDefinitely/SetArgumentMaybe means
437 // that someone set the argument values out-of-band, and currently this always means setting to a
438 // non-clear value.
439 ASSERT(!m_state.operand(node->operand()).isClear());
440 break;
441
442 case InitializeEntrypointArguments: {
443 unsigned entrypointIndex = node->entrypointIndex();
444 const Vector<FlushFormat>& argumentFormats = m_graph.m_argumentFormats[entrypointIndex];
445 for (unsigned argument = 0; argument < argumentFormats.size(); ++argument) {
446 AbstractValue& value = m_state.argument(argument);
447 switch (argumentFormats[argument]) {
448 case FlushedInt32:
449 value.setNonCellType(SpecInt32Only);
450 break;
451 case FlushedBoolean:
452 value.setNonCellType(SpecBoolean);
453 break;
454 case FlushedCell:
455 value.setType(m_graph, SpecCellCheck);
456 break;
457 case FlushedJSValue:
458 value.makeBytecodeTop();
459 break;
460 default:
461 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Bad flush format for argument");
462 break;
463 }
464 }
465 break;
466 }
467
468 case VarargsLength: {
469 clobberWorld();
470 setTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
471 break;
472 }
473
474 case LoadVarargs:
475 case ForwardVarargs: {
476 // FIXME: ForwardVarargs should check if the count becomes known, and if it does, it should turn
477 // itself into a straight-line sequence of GetStack/PutStack.
478 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=143071
479 switch (node->op()) {
480 case LoadVarargs:
481 clobberWorld();
482 break;
483 case ForwardVarargs:
484 break;
485 default:
486 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Bad opcode");
487 break;
488 }
489 LoadVarargsData* data = node->loadVarargsData();
490 m_state.operand(data->count).setNonCellType(SpecInt32Only);
491 for (unsigned i = data->limit - 1; i--;)
492 m_state.operand(data->start + i).makeHeapTop();
493 break;
494 }
495
496 case ValueBitNot: {
497 JSValue operand = forNode(node->child1()).value();
498 if (operand && operand.isInt32()) {
499 didFoldClobberWorld();
500 int32_t a = operand.asInt32();
501 setConstant(node, JSValue(~a));
502 break;
503 }
504
505 if (node->child1().useKind() == BigInt32Use) {
506#if USE(BIGINT32)
507 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt32);
508#else
509 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
510#endif
511 } else if (node->child1().useKind() == HeapBigIntUse) {
512 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
513 // the format of our result:
514 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
515 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
516 } else if (node->child1().useKind() == AnyBigIntUse)
517 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
518 else {
519 clobberWorld();
520 setTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only | SpecBigInt);
521 }
522
523 break;
524 }
525
526 case ArithBitNot: {
527 JSValue operand = forNode(node->child1()).value();
528 if (operand && operand.isInt32()) {
529 int32_t a = operand.asInt32();
530 setConstant(node, JSValue(~a));
531 break;
532 }
533
534 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
535 break;
536 }
537
538 case ValueBitXor:
539 case ValueBitAnd:
540 case ValueBitOr:
541 case ValueBitRShift:
542 case ValueBitLShift: {
543 if (handleConstantBinaryBitwiseOp(node))
544 break;
545
546 // FIXME: this use of binaryUseKind means that we cannot specialize to (for example) a HeapBigInt left-operand and a BigInt32 right-operand.
547 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210977
548 if (node->binaryUseKind() == BigInt32Use) {
549#if USE(BIGINT32)
550 switch (node->op()) {
551 case ValueBitXor:
552 case ValueBitAnd:
553 case ValueBitOr:
554 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt32);
555 break;
556
557 // FIXME: We should have inlined implementation that always returns BigInt32.
558 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210847
559 case ValueBitRShift:
560 case ValueBitLShift:
561 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
562 break;
563 default:
564 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Incorrect DFG op");
565 }
566#else
567 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "No BigInt32 support");
568#endif
569 } else if (node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)) {
570 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
571 // the format of our result:
572 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
573 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
574 } else if (node->binaryUseKind() == AnyBigIntUse)
575 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
576 else {
577 clobberWorld();
578 setTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only | SpecBigInt);
579 }
580 break;
581 }
582
583 case ArithBitAnd:
584 case ArithBitOr:
585 case ArithBitXor:
586 case ArithBitRShift:
587 case ArithBitLShift:
588 case BitURShift: {
589 if (node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse || node->child2().useKind() == UntypedUse) {
590 clobberWorld();
591 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
592 break;
593 }
594
595 if (handleConstantBinaryBitwiseOp(node))
596 break;
597
598 if (node->op() == ArithBitAnd
599 && (isBoolInt32Speculation(forNode(node->child1()).m_type) ||
600 isBoolInt32Speculation(forNode(node->child2()).m_type))) {
601 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolInt32);
602 break;
603 }
604
605 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
606 break;
607 }
608
609 case UInt32ToNumber: {
610 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
611 if (doesOverflow(node->arithMode())) {
612 if (enableInt52()) {
613 if (child && child.isAnyInt()) {
614 int64_t machineInt = child.asAnyInt();
615 setConstant(node, jsNumber(static_cast<uint32_t>(machineInt)));
616 break;
617 }
618 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
619 break;
620 }
621 if (child && child.isInt32()) {
622 uint32_t value = child.asInt32();
623 setConstant(node, jsNumber(value));
624 break;
625 }
626 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecAnyIntAsDouble);
627 break;
628 }
629 if (child && child.isInt32()) {
630 int32_t value = child.asInt32();
631 if (value >= 0) {
632 setConstant(node, jsNumber(value));
633 break;
634 }
635 }
636 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
637 break;
638 }
639
640 case BooleanToNumber: {
641 JSValue concreteValue = forNode(node->child1()).value();
642 if (concreteValue) {
643 if (concreteValue.isBoolean())
644 setConstant(node, jsNumber(concreteValue.asBoolean()));
645 else
646 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(concreteValue));
647 break;
648 }
649 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node);
650 value = forNode(node->child1());
651 if (node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse && !(value.m_type & ~SpecBoolean))
652 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
653 if (value.m_type & SpecBoolean) {
654 value.merge(SpecBoolInt32);
655 value.filter(~SpecBoolean);
656 }
657 break;
658 }
659
660 case DoubleAsInt32: {
661 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
662 if (child && child.isNumber()) {
663 double asDouble = child.asNumber();
664 int32_t asInt = JSC::toInt32(asDouble);
665 if (bitwise_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<double>(asInt)) == bitwise_cast<int64_t>(asDouble)) {
666 setConstant(node, JSValue(asInt));
667 break;
668 }
669 }
670 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
671 break;
672 }
673
674 case ValueToInt32: {
675 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
676 if (child) {
677 if (child.isNumber()) {
678 if (child.isInt32())
679 setConstant(node, child);
680 else
681 setConstant(node, JSValue(JSC::toInt32(child.asDouble())));
682 break;
683 }
684 if (child.isBoolean()) {
685 setConstant(node, jsNumber(child.asBoolean()));
686 break;
687 }
688 if (child.isUndefinedOrNull()) {
689 setConstant(node, jsNumber(0));
690 break;
691 }
692 }
693
694 if (isBooleanSpeculation(forNode(node->child1()).m_type)) {
695 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolInt32);
696 break;
697 }
698
699 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
700 break;
701 }
702
703 case DoubleRep: {
704 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
705 if (std::optional<double> number = child.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
706 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(*number));
707 break;
708 }
709
710 SpeculatedType type = forNode(node->child1()).m_type;
711 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
712 case NotCellNorBigIntUse: {
713 if (type & SpecOther) {
714 type &= ~SpecOther;
715 type |= SpecDoublePureNaN | SpecBoolInt32; // Null becomes zero, undefined becomes NaN.
716 }
717 if (type & SpecBoolean) {
718 type &= ~SpecBoolean;
719 type |= SpecBoolInt32; // True becomes 1, false becomes 0.
720 }
721 type &= SpecBytecodeNumber;
722 break;
723 }
724
725 case Int52RepUse:
726 case NumberUse:
727 case RealNumberUse:
728 break;
729
730 default:
731 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
732 }
733 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, type);
734 forNode(node).fixTypeForRepresentation(m_graph, node);
735 break;
736 }
737
738 case Int52Rep: {
739 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
740 if (child && child.isAnyInt()) {
741 setConstant(node, child);
742 break;
743 }
744
745 setTypeForNode(node, forNode(node->child1()).m_type);
746 forNode(node).fixTypeForRepresentation(m_graph, node);
747 break;
748 }
749
750 case ValueRep: {
751 JSValue value = forNode(node->child1()).value();
752 if (value) {
753 setConstant(node, value);
754 break;
755 }
756
757 setTypeForNode(node, forNode(node->child1()).m_type & ~SpecDoubleImpureNaN);
758 forNode(node).fixTypeForRepresentation(m_graph, node);
759 break;
760 }
761
762 case ValueSub:
763 case ValueAdd: {
764 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)) {
765 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
766 // the format of our result:
767 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
768 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
769 } else if (node->isBinaryUseKind(AnyBigIntUse))
770 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
771 else if (node->isBinaryUseKind(BigInt32Use))
772 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt32);
773 else {
774 DFG_ASSERT(m_graph, node, node->binaryUseKind() == UntypedUse);
775 clobberWorld();
776 // FIXME: do we really need SpecString here for ValueSub? It seems like we only need it for ValueAdd.
777 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString | SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
778 }
779 break;
780 }
781
782 case StrCat: {
783 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
784 break;
785 }
786
787 case ArithAdd: {
788 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
789 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
790 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
791 case Int32Use:
792 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
793 if (!shouldCheckOverflow(node->arithMode())) {
794 setConstant(node, jsNumber(left.asInt32() + right.asInt32()));
795 break;
796 }
797 JSValue result = jsNumber(left.asNumber() + right.asNumber());
798 if (result.isInt32()) {
799 setConstant(node, result);
800 break;
801 }
802 }
803 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
804 break;
805 case Int52RepUse:
806 if (left && right && left.isAnyInt() && right.isAnyInt()) {
807 JSValue result = jsNumber(left.asAnyInt() + right.asAnyInt());
808 if (result.isAnyInt()) {
809 setConstant(node, result);
810 break;
811 }
812 }
813 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
814 break;
815 case DoubleRepUse:
816 if (left && right && left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
817 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(left.asNumber() + right.asNumber()));
818 break;
819 }
820 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
821 typeOfDoubleSum(
822 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
823 break;
824 default:
825 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
826 break;
827 }
828 break;
829 }
830
831 case AtomicsIsLockFree: {
832 if (m_graph.child(node, 0).useKind() != Int32Use)
833 clobberWorld();
834 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
835 break;
836 }
837
838 case ArithClz32: {
839 JSValue operand = forNode(node->child1()).value();
840 if (std::optional<double> number = operand.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
841 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
842 case Int32Use:
843 case KnownInt32Use:
844 break;
845 default:
846 didFoldClobberWorld();
847 break;
848 }
849 uint32_t value = toUInt32(*number);
850 setConstant(node, jsNumber(clz(value)));
851 break;
852 }
853 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
854 case Int32Use:
855 case KnownInt32Use:
856 break;
857 default:
858 clobberWorld();
859 break;
860 }
861 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
862 break;
863 }
864
865 case MakeRope: {
866 unsigned numberOfRemovedChildren = 0;
867 for (unsigned i = 0; i < AdjacencyList::Size; ++i) {
868 Edge& edge = node->children.child(i);
869 if (!edge)
870 break;
871 JSValue childConstant = m_state.forNode(edge).value();
872 if (!childConstant)
873 continue;
874 if (!childConstant.isString())
875 continue;
876 if (asString(childConstant)->length())
877 continue;
878 ++numberOfRemovedChildren;
879 }
880
881 if (numberOfRemovedChildren)
882 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
883 setForNode(node, m_vm.stringStructure.get());
884 break;
885 }
886
887 case ArithSub: {
888 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
889 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
890 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
891 case Int32Use:
892 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
893 if (!shouldCheckOverflow(node->arithMode())) {
894 setConstant(node, jsNumber(left.asInt32() - right.asInt32()));
895 break;
896 }
897 JSValue result = jsNumber(left.asNumber() - right.asNumber());
898 if (result.isInt32()) {
899 setConstant(node, result);
900 break;
901 }
902 }
903 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
904 break;
905 case Int52RepUse:
906 if (left && right && left.isAnyInt() && right.isAnyInt()) {
907 JSValue result = jsNumber(left.asAnyInt() - right.asAnyInt());
908 if (result.isAnyInt()) {
909 setConstant(node, result);
910 break;
911 }
912 }
913 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
914 break;
915 case DoubleRepUse:
916 if (left && right && left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
917 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(left.asNumber() - right.asNumber()));
918 break;
919 }
920 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
921 typeOfDoubleDifference(
922 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
923 break;
924 case UntypedUse:
925 clobberWorld();
926 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber);
927 break;
928 default:
929 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
930 break;
931 }
932 break;
933 }
934
935 case ValueNegate: {
936 // FIXME: we could do much smarter things for BigInts, see ValueAdd/ValueSub.
937 clobberWorld();
938 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
939 break;
940 }
941
942 case ArithNegate: {
943 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
944 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
945 case Int32Use:
946 if (child && child.isInt32()) {
947 if (!shouldCheckOverflow(node->arithMode())) {
948 setConstant(node, jsNumber(-child.asInt32()));
949 break;
950 }
951 double doubleResult;
952 if (shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithMode()))
953 doubleResult = -child.asNumber();
954 else
955 doubleResult = 0 - child.asNumber();
956 JSValue valueResult = jsNumber(doubleResult);
957 if (valueResult.isInt32()) {
958 setConstant(node, valueResult);
959 break;
960 }
961 }
962 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
963 break;
964 case Int52RepUse:
965 if (child && child.isAnyInt()) {
966 double doubleResult;
967 if (shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithMode()))
968 doubleResult = -child.asNumber();
969 else
970 doubleResult = 0 - child.asNumber();
971 JSValue valueResult = jsNumber(doubleResult);
972 if (valueResult.isAnyInt()) {
973 setConstant(node, valueResult);
974 break;
975 }
976 }
977 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
978 break;
979 case DoubleRepUse:
980 if (child && child.isNumber()) {
981 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(-child.asNumber()));
982 break;
983 }
984 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
985 typeOfDoubleNegation(
986 forNode(node->child1()).m_type));
987 break;
988 default:
989 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
990 break;
991 }
992 break;
993 }
994
995 case Inc:
996 case Dec: {
997 // FIXME: support some form of constant folding here.
998 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=204258
999 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
1000 case Int32Use:
1001 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1002 break;
1003 case Int52RepUse:
1004 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
1005 break;
1006 case DoubleRepUse:
1007 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, typeOfDoubleIncOrDec(forNode(node->child1()).m_type));
1008 break;
1009 case HeapBigIntUse:
1010 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
1011 // the format of our result:
1012 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
1013 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1014 break;
1015 case AnyBigIntUse:
1016 case BigInt32Use:
1017 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1018 break;
1019 default:
1020 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
1021 clobberWorld(); // Because of the call to ToNumeric()
1022 break;
1023 }
1024 break;
1025 }
1026
1027 case ValuePow: {
1028 JSValue childX = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1029 JSValue childY = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1030 if (childX && childY && childX.isNumber() && childY.isNumber()) {
1031 // We need to call `didFoldClobberWorld` here because this path is only possible
1032 // when node->useKind is UntypedUse. In the case of AnyBigIntUse or friends, children will be
1033 // cleared by `AbstractInterpreter::executeEffects`.
1034 didFoldClobberWorld();
1035 // Our boxing scheme here matches what we do in operationValuePow.
1036 setConstant(node, jsNumber(operationMathPow(childX.asNumber(), childY.asNumber())));
1037 break;
1038 }
1039
1040 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)) {
1041 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
1042 // the format of our result:
1043 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
1044 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1045 } else if (node->binaryUseKind() == AnyBigIntUse || node->binaryUseKind() == BigInt32Use)
1046 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1047 else {
1048 clobberWorld();
1049 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
1050 }
1051 break;
1052 }
1053
1054 case ValueMul: {
1055 // FIXME: why is this code not shared with ValueSub?
1056 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)) {
1057 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
1058 // the format of our result:
1059 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
1060 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1061 } else if (node->isBinaryUseKind(AnyBigIntUse))
1062 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1063 else if (node->isBinaryUseKind(BigInt32Use))
1064 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt32);
1065 else {
1066 clobberWorld();
1067 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
1068 }
1069 break;
1070 }
1071
1072 case ArithMul: {
1073 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1074 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1075 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
1076 case Int32Use:
1077 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
1078 if (!shouldCheckOverflow(node->arithMode())) {
1079 setConstant(node, jsNumber(left.asInt32() * right.asInt32()));
1080 break;
1081 }
1082 double doubleResult = left.asNumber() * right.asNumber();
1083 if (!shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithMode()))
1084 doubleResult += 0; // Sanitizes zero.
1085 JSValue valueResult = jsNumber(doubleResult);
1086 if (valueResult.isInt32()) {
1087 setConstant(node, valueResult);
1088 break;
1089 }
1090 }
1091 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1092 break;
1093 case Int52RepUse:
1094 if (left && right && left.isAnyInt() && right.isAnyInt()) {
1095 double doubleResult = left.asNumber() * right.asNumber();
1096 if (!shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithMode()))
1097 doubleResult += 0;
1098 JSValue valueResult = jsNumber(doubleResult);
1099 if (valueResult.isAnyInt()) {
1100 setConstant(node, valueResult);
1101 break;
1102 }
1103 }
1104 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
1105 break;
1106 case DoubleRepUse:
1107 if (left && right && left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
1108 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(left.asNumber() * right.asNumber()));
1109 break;
1110 }
1111 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
1112 typeOfDoubleProduct(
1113 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1114 break;
1115 default:
1116 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1117 break;
1118 }
1119 break;
1120 }
1121
1122 case ValueMod:
1123 case ValueDiv: {
1124 if (handleConstantDivOp(node))
1125 break;
1126
1127 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)) {
1128 // FIXME: We will want an arithmetic mode here that allows us to speculate or dictate
1129 // the format of our result:
1130 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=210982
1131 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1132 } else if (node->binaryUseKind() == AnyBigIntUse || node->binaryUseKind() == BigInt32Use)
1133 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBigInt);
1134 else {
1135 clobberWorld();
1136 setTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber | SpecBigInt);
1137 }
1138 break;
1139 }
1140
1141 case ArithMod:
1142 case ArithDiv: {
1143 if (handleConstantDivOp(node))
1144 break;
1145
1146 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
1147 case Int32Use:
1148 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1149 break;
1150 case DoubleRepUse:
1151 if (node->op() == ArithDiv) {
1152 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
1153 typeOfDoubleQuotient(
1154 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1155 } else {
1156 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
1157 typeOfDoubleBinaryOp(
1158 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1159 }
1160
1161 break;
1162 default:
1163 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1164 break;
1165 }
1166 break;
1167 }
1168
1169 case ArithMin: {
1170 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1171 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1172 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
1173 case Int32Use:
1174 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
1175 setConstant(node, jsNumber(std::min(left.asInt32(), right.asInt32())));
1176 break;
1177 }
1178 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1179 break;
1180 case DoubleRepUse:
1181 if (left && right && left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
1182 double a = left.asNumber();
1183 double b = right.asNumber();
1184 // The spec for Math.min states that +0 is considered to be larger than -0.
1185 double result = a < b || (!a && !b && std::signbit(a)) ? a : (b <= a ? b : a + b);
1186 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(result));
1187 break;
1188 }
1189 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
1190 typeOfDoubleMinMax(
1191 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1192 break;
1193 default:
1194 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1195 break;
1196 }
1197 break;
1198 }
1199
1200 case ArithMax: {
1201 JSValue left = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1202 JSValue right = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1203 switch (node->binaryUseKind()) {
1204 case Int32Use:
1205 if (left && right && left.isInt32() && right.isInt32()) {
1206 setConstant(node, jsNumber(std::max(left.asInt32(), right.asInt32())));
1207 break;
1208 }
1209 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1210 break;
1211 case DoubleRepUse:
1212 if (left && right && left.isNumber() && right.isNumber()) {
1213 double a = left.asNumber();
1214 double b = right.asNumber();
1215 // The spec for Math.max states that +0 is considered to be larger than -0.
1216 double result = a > b || (!a && !b && !std::signbit(a)) ? a : (b >= a ? b : a + b);
1217 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(result));
1218 break;
1219 }
1220 setNonCellTypeForNode(node,
1221 typeOfDoubleMinMax(
1222 forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1223 break;
1224 default:
1225 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1226 break;
1227 }
1228 break;
1229 }
1230
1231 case ArithAbs: {
1232 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1233 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
1234 case Int32Use:
1235 if (std::optional<double> number = child.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
1236 JSValue result = jsNumber(fabs(*number));
1237 if (result.isInt32()) {
1238 setConstant(node, result);
1239 break;
1240 }
1241 }
1242 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1243 break;
1244 case DoubleRepUse:
1245 if (std::optional<double> number = child.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
1246 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(fabs(*number)));
1247 break;
1248 }
1249 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, typeOfDoubleAbs(forNode(node->child1()).m_type));
1250 break;
1251 default:
1252 DFG_ASSERT(m_graph, node, node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse, node->child1().useKind());
1253 clobberWorld();
1254 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber);
1255 break;
1256 }
1257 break;
1258 }
1259
1260 case ArithPow: {
1261 JSValue childY = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1262 if (childY && childY.isNumber()) {
1263 if (!childY.asNumber()) {
1264 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(1));
1265 break;
1266 }
1267
1268 JSValue childX = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1269 if (childX && childX.isNumber()) {
1270 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(operationMathPow(childX.asNumber(), childY.asNumber())));
1271 break;
1272 }
1273 }
1274 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, typeOfDoublePow(forNode(node->child1()).m_type, forNode(node->child2()).m_type));
1275 break;
1276 }
1277
1278 case ArithRandom: {
1279 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecDoubleReal);
1280 break;
1281 }
1282
1283 case ArithRound:
1284 case ArithFloor:
1285 case ArithCeil:
1286 case ArithTrunc: {
1287 JSValue operand = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1288 if (std::optional<double> number = operand.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
1289 if (node->child1().useKind() != DoubleRepUse)
1290 didFoldClobberWorld();
1291
1292 double roundedValue = 0;
1293 if (node->op() == ArithRound)
1294 roundedValue = Math::roundDouble(*number);
1295 else if (node->op() == ArithFloor)
1296 roundedValue = Math::floorDouble(*number);
1297 else if (node->op() == ArithCeil)
1298 roundedValue = Math::ceilDouble(*number);
1299 else {
1300 ASSERT(node->op() == ArithTrunc);
1301 roundedValue = trunc(*number);
1302 }
1303
1304 if (node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse) {
1305 setConstant(node, jsNumber(roundedValue));
1306 break;
1307 }
1308 if (producesInteger(node->arithRoundingMode())) {
1309 int32_t roundedValueAsInt32 = static_cast<int32_t>(roundedValue);
1310 if (roundedValueAsInt32 == roundedValue) {
1311 if (shouldCheckNegativeZero(node->arithRoundingMode())) {
1312 if (roundedValueAsInt32 || !std::signbit(roundedValue)) {
1313 setConstant(node, jsNumber(roundedValueAsInt32));
1314 break;
1315 }
1316 } else {
1317 setConstant(node, jsNumber(roundedValueAsInt32));
1318 break;
1319 }
1320 }
1321 } else {
1322 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(roundedValue));
1323 break;
1324 }
1325 }
1326 if (node->child1().useKind() == DoubleRepUse) {
1327 if (producesInteger(node->arithRoundingMode()))
1328 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1329 else if (node->child1().useKind() == DoubleRepUse)
1330 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, typeOfDoubleRounding(forNode(node->child1()).m_type));
1331 } else {
1332 DFG_ASSERT(m_graph, node, node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse, node->child1().useKind());
1333 clobberWorld();
1334 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber);
1335 }
1336 break;
1337 }
1338
1339 case ArithSqrt:
1340 executeDoubleUnaryOpEffects(node, sqrt);
1341 break;
1342
1343 case ArithFRound:
1344 executeDoubleUnaryOpEffects(node, [](double value) -> double { return static_cast<float>(value); });
1345 break;
1346
1347 case ArithUnary:
1348 executeDoubleUnaryOpEffects(node, arithUnaryFunction(node->arithUnaryType()));
1349 break;
1350
1351 case ToBoolean:
1352 case LogicalNot: {
1353 TriState result = booleanResult(node, forNode(node->child1()));
1354 if (result == TriState::Indeterminate) {
1355 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
1356 break;
1357 }
1358
1359 bool resultAsBool = result == TriState::True;
1360 if (node->op() == LogicalNot)
1361 resultAsBool = !resultAsBool;
1362 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(resultAsBool));
1363 break;
1364 }
1365
1366 case MapHash: {
1367 if (JSValue key = forNode(node->child1()).value()) {
1368 if (std::optional<uint32_t> hash = concurrentJSMapHash(key)) {
1369 // Although C++ code uses uint32_t for the hash, the closest type in DFG IR is Int32
1370 // and that's what MapHash returns. So, we have to cast to int32_t to avoid large
1371 // unsigned values becoming doubles. This casting between signed and unsigned
1372 // happens in the assembly code we emit when we don't constant fold this node.
1373 setConstant(node, jsNumber(static_cast<int32_t>(*hash)));
1374 break;
1375 }
1376 }
1377 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
1378 break;
1379 }
1380
1381 case NormalizeMapKey: {
1382 if (JSValue key = forNode(node->child1()).value()) {
1383 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(normalizeMapKey(key)));
1384 break;
1385 }
1386
1387 SpeculatedType typesNeedingNormalization = (SpecFullNumber & ~SpecInt32Only) | SpecHeapBigInt;
1388 if (!(forNode(node->child1()).m_type & typesNeedingNormalization)) {
1389 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
1390 forNode(node) = forNode(node->child1());
1391 break;
1392 }
1393
1394 makeHeapTopForNode(node);
1395 break;
1396 }
1397
1398 case StringValueOf: {
1399 clobberWorld();
1400 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
1401 break;
1402 }
1403
1404 case StringSlice: {
1405 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
1406 break;
1407 }
1408
1409 case ToLowerCase: {
1410 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
1411 break;
1412 }
1413
1414 case LoadKeyFromMapBucket:
1415 case LoadValueFromMapBucket:
1416 case ExtractValueFromWeakMapGet:
1417 makeHeapTopForNode(node);
1418 break;
1419
1420 case GetMapBucket:
1421 case GetMapBucketHead:
1422 if (node->child1().useKind() == MapObjectUse)
1423 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketMapStructure.get());
1424 else {
1425 ASSERT(node->child1().useKind() == SetObjectUse);
1426 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketSetStructure.get());
1427 }
1428 break;
1429
1430 case GetMapBucketNext:
1431 if (node->bucketOwnerType() == BucketOwnerType::Map)
1432 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketMapStructure.get());
1433 else {
1434 ASSERT(node->bucketOwnerType() == BucketOwnerType::Set);
1435 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketSetStructure.get());
1436 }
1437 break;
1438
1439 case SetAdd:
1440 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketSetStructure.get());
1441 break;
1442
1443 case MapSet:
1444 setForNode(node, m_vm.hashMapBucketMapStructure.get());
1445 break;
1446
1447 case WeakSetAdd:
1448 case WeakMapSet:
1449 break;
1450
1451 case WeakMapGet:
1452 makeBytecodeTopForNode(node);
1453 break;
1454
1455 case IsEmpty:
1456 case TypeOfIsUndefined:
1457 case TypeOfIsObject:
1458 case TypeOfIsFunction:
1459 case IsUndefinedOrNull:
1460 case IsBoolean:
1461 case IsNumber:
1462 case IsBigInt:
1463 case NumberIsInteger:
1464 case IsObject:
1465 case IsCallable:
1466 case IsConstructor:
1467 case IsCellWithType:
1468 case IsTypedArrayView: {
1469 AbstractValue child = forNode(node->child1());
1470 if (child.value()) {
1471 bool constantWasSet = true;
1472 switch (node->op()) {
1473 case IsCellWithType:
1474 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isCell() && child.value().asCell()->type() == node->queriedType()));
1475 break;
1476 case TypeOfIsUndefined:
1477 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(
1478 child.value().isCell()
1479 ? child.value().asCell()->structure(m_vm)->masqueradesAsUndefined(m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic))
1480 : child.value().isUndefined()));
1481 break;
1482 case TypeOfIsObject: {
1483 TriState result = jsTypeofIsObjectWithConcurrency<Concurrency::ConcurrentThread>(m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic), child.value());
1484 if (result != TriState::Indeterminate)
1485 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result == TriState::True));
1486 else
1487 constantWasSet = false;
1488 break;
1489 }
1490 case TypeOfIsFunction: {
1491 TriState result = jsTypeofIsFunctionWithConcurrency<Concurrency::ConcurrentThread>(m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic), child.value());
1492 if (result != TriState::Indeterminate)
1493 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result == TriState::True));
1494 else
1495 constantWasSet = false;
1496 break;
1497 }
1498 case IsUndefinedOrNull:
1499 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isUndefinedOrNull()));
1500 break;
1501 case IsBoolean:
1502 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isBoolean()));
1503 break;
1504 case IsNumber:
1505 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isNumber()));
1506 break;
1507 case IsBigInt:
1508 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isBigInt()));
1509 break;
1510 case NumberIsInteger:
1511 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(NumberConstructor::isIntegerImpl(child.value())));
1512 break;
1513 case IsObject:
1514 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isObject()));
1515 break;
1516 case IsCallable: {
1517 TriState result = child.value().isCallableWithConcurrency<Concurrency::ConcurrentThread>(m_vm);
1518 if (result != TriState::Indeterminate)
1519 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result == TriState::True));
1520 else
1521 constantWasSet = false;
1522 break;
1523 }
1524 case IsConstructor: {
1525 TriState result = child.value().isConstructorWithConcurrency<Concurrency::ConcurrentThread>(m_vm);
1526 if (result != TriState::Indeterminate)
1527 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result == TriState::True));
1528 else
1529 constantWasSet = false;
1530 break;
1531 }
1532 case IsEmpty:
1533 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isEmpty()));
1534 break;
1535 case IsTypedArrayView:
1536 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(child.value().isObject() && isTypedView(child.value().getObject()->classInfo(m_vm)->typedArrayStorageType)));
1537 break;
1538 default:
1539 constantWasSet = false;
1540 break;
1541 }
1542 if (constantWasSet)
1543 break;
1544 }
1545
1546 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecCell)) {
1547 if (child.m_structure.isFinite()) {
1548 bool constantWasSet = false;
1549 switch (node->op()) {
1550 case IsCellWithType: {
1551 bool ok = true;
1552 std::optional<bool> result;
1553 child.m_structure.forEach(
1554 [&] (RegisteredStructure structure) {
1555 bool matched = structure->typeInfo().type() == node->queriedType();
1556 if (!result)
1557 result = matched;
1558 else {
1559 if (result.value() != matched)
1560 ok = false;
1561 }
1562 });
1563 if (ok && result) {
1564 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result.value()));
1565 constantWasSet = true;
1566 }
1567 break;
1568 }
1569 default:
1570 break;
1571 }
1572 if (constantWasSet)
1573 break;
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 // FIXME: This code should really use AbstractValue::isType() and
1578 // AbstractValue::couldBeType().
1579 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=146870
1580
1581 bool constantWasSet = false;
1582 switch (node->op()) {
1583 case IsEmpty: {
1584 if (child.m_type && !(child.m_type & SpecEmpty)) {
1585 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1586 constantWasSet = true;
1587 break;
1588 }
1589
1590 if (child.m_type && !(child.m_type & ~SpecEmpty)) {
1591 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1592 constantWasSet = true;
1593 break;
1594 }
1595
1596 break;
1597 }
1598 case TypeOfIsUndefined:
1599 // FIXME: Use the masquerades-as-undefined watchpoint thingy.
1600 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=144456
1601
1602 if (!(child.m_type & (SpecOther | SpecObjectOther))) {
1603 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1604 constantWasSet = true;
1605 break;
1606 }
1607
1608 break;
1609 case TypeOfIsObject:
1610 // FIXME: Use the masquerades-as-undefined watchpoint thingy.
1611 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=144456
1612
1613 // These expressions are complicated to parse. A helpful way to parse this is that
1614 // "!(T & ~S)" means "T is a subset of S". Conversely, "!(T & S)" means "T is a
1615 // disjoint set from S". Things like "T - S" means that, provided that S is a
1616 // subset of T, it's the "set of all things in T but not in S". Things like "T | S"
1617 // mean the "union of T and S".
1618
1619 // Is the child's type an object that isn't an other-object (i.e. object that could
1620 // have masquaredes-as-undefined traps) and isn't a function? Then: we should fold
1621 // this to true.
1622 if (!(child.m_type & ~(SpecObject - SpecObjectOther - SpecFunction))) {
1623 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1624 constantWasSet = true;
1625 break;
1626 }
1627
1628 // Is the child's type definitely not either of: an object that isn't a function,
1629 // or either undefined or null? Then: we should fold this to false. This means
1630 // for example that if it's any non-function object, including those that have
1631 // masquerades-as-undefined traps, then we don't fold. It also means we won't fold
1632 // if it's undefined-or-null, since the type bits don't distinguish between
1633 // undefined (which should fold to false) and null (which should fold to true).
1634 if (!(child.m_type & ((SpecObject - SpecFunction) | SpecOther))) {
1635 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1636 constantWasSet = true;
1637 break;
1638 }
1639
1640 break;
1641 case IsUndefinedOrNull:
1642 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecOther)) {
1643 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1644 constantWasSet = true;
1645 break;
1646 }
1647
1648 if (!(child.m_type & SpecOther)) {
1649 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1650 constantWasSet = true;
1651 break;
1652 }
1653 break;
1654 case IsBoolean:
1655 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecBoolean)) {
1656 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1657 constantWasSet = true;
1658 break;
1659 }
1660
1661 if (!(child.m_type & SpecBoolean)) {
1662 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1663 constantWasSet = true;
1664 break;
1665 }
1666
1667 break;
1668 case IsNumber:
1669 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecFullNumber)) {
1670 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1671 constantWasSet = true;
1672 break;
1673 }
1674
1675 if (!(child.m_type & SpecFullNumber)) {
1676 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1677 constantWasSet = true;
1678 break;
1679 }
1680
1681 break;
1682 case IsBigInt:
1683 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecBigInt)) {
1684 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1685 constantWasSet = true;
1686 break;
1687 }
1688
1689 if (!(child.m_type & SpecBigInt)) {
1690 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1691 constantWasSet = true;
1692 break;
1693 }
1694
1695 // FIXME: if the SpeculatedType informs us that we won't have a BigInt32 (or that we won't have a HeapBigInt), then we can transform this node into a IsCellWithType(HeapBigIntType) (or a hypothetical IsBigInt32 node).
1696
1697 break;
1698 case NumberIsInteger:
1699 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecInt32Only)) {
1700 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1701 constantWasSet = true;
1702 break;
1703 }
1704
1705 if (!(child.m_type & SpecFullNumber)) {
1706 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1707 constantWasSet = true;
1708 break;
1709 }
1710
1711 break;
1712
1713 case IsObject:
1714 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecObject)) {
1715 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1716 constantWasSet = true;
1717 break;
1718 }
1719
1720 if (!(child.m_type & SpecObject)) {
1721 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1722 constantWasSet = true;
1723 break;
1724 }
1725
1726 break;
1727 case TypeOfIsFunction:
1728 case IsCallable:
1729 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecFunction)) {
1730 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1731 constantWasSet = true;
1732 break;
1733 }
1734
1735 if (!(child.m_type & (SpecFunction | SpecObjectOther | SpecProxyObject))) {
1736 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1737 constantWasSet = true;
1738 break;
1739 }
1740 break;
1741
1742 case IsConstructor:
1743 // FIXME: We can speculate constructability from child's m_structure.
1744 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=211796
1745 break;
1746
1747 case IsCellWithType: {
1748 std::optional<SpeculatedType> filter = node->speculatedTypeForQuery();
1749 if (!filter) {
1750 if (!(child.m_type & SpecCell)) {
1751 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1752 constantWasSet = true;
1753 }
1754 break;
1755 }
1756 if (!(child.m_type & ~filter.value())) {
1757 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1758 constantWasSet = true;
1759 break;
1760 }
1761 if (!(child.m_type & filter.value())) {
1762 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1763 constantWasSet = true;
1764 break;
1765 }
1766 break;
1767 }
1768
1769 case IsTypedArrayView:
1770 if (!(child.m_type & ~SpecTypedArrayView)) {
1771 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1772 constantWasSet = true;
1773 break;
1774 }
1775 if (!(child.m_type & SpecTypedArrayView)) {
1776 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1777 constantWasSet = true;
1778 break;
1779 }
1780 break;
1781
1782 default:
1783 break;
1784 }
1785 if (constantWasSet)
1786 break;
1787
1788 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
1789 break;
1790 }
1791
1792 case TypeOf: {
1793 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1794 AbstractValue& abstractChild = forNode(node->child1());
1795 if (child) {
1796 if (JSString* typeString = jsTypeStringForValueWithConcurrency(m_vm, m_codeBlock->globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic), child, Concurrency::ConcurrentThread)) {
1797 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(typeString));
1798 break;
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 if (isFullNumberSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1803 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.numberString()));
1804 break;
1805 }
1806
1807 if (isStringSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1808 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.stringString()));
1809 break;
1810 }
1811
1812 // FIXME: We could use the masquerades-as-undefined watchpoint here.
1813 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=144456
1814 if (!(abstractChild.m_type & ~(SpecObject - SpecObjectOther - SpecFunction))) {
1815 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.objectString()));
1816 break;
1817 }
1818
1819 if (isFunctionSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1820 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.functionString()));
1821 break;
1822 }
1823
1824 if (isBooleanSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1825 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.booleanString()));
1826 break;
1827 }
1828
1829 if (isSymbolSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1830 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.symbolString()));
1831 break;
1832 }
1833
1834 if (isBigIntSpeculation(abstractChild.m_type)) {
1835 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(m_vm.smallStrings.bigintString()));
1836 break;
1837 }
1838
1839 setTypeForNode(node, SpecStringIdent);
1840 break;
1841 }
1842
1843 case CompareBelow:
1844 case CompareBelowEq: {
1845 JSValue leftConst = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1846 JSValue rightConst = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1847 if (leftConst && rightConst) {
1848 if (leftConst.isInt32() && rightConst.isInt32()) {
1849 uint32_t a = static_cast<uint32_t>(leftConst.asInt32());
1850 uint32_t b = static_cast<uint32_t>(rightConst.asInt32());
1851 switch (node->op()) {
1852 case CompareBelow:
1853 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(a < b));
1854 break;
1855 case CompareBelowEq:
1856 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(a <= b));
1857 break;
1858 default:
1859 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1860 break;
1861 }
1862 break;
1863 }
1864 }
1865
1866 if (node->child1() == node->child2()) {
1867 switch (node->op()) {
1868 case CompareBelow:
1869 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1870 break;
1871 case CompareBelowEq:
1872 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1873 break;
1874 default:
1875 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Unexpected node type");
1876 break;
1877 }
1878 break;
1879 }
1880 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
1881 break;
1882 }
1883
1884 case CompareLess:
1885 case CompareLessEq:
1886 case CompareGreater:
1887 case CompareGreaterEq:
1888 case CompareEq: {
1889 bool isClobbering = node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse);
1890
1891 if (isClobbering)
1892 didFoldClobberWorld();
1893
1894 JSValue leftConst = forNode(node->child1()).value();
1895 JSValue rightConst = forNode(node->child2()).value();
1896 if (leftConst && rightConst) {
1897 if (leftConst.isNumber() && rightConst.isNumber()) {
1898 auto compareNumber = [&](double a, double b) {
1899 switch (node->op()) {
1900 case CompareLess:
1901 return jsBoolean(a < b);
1902 case CompareLessEq:
1903 return jsBoolean(a <= b);
1904 case CompareGreater:
1905 return jsBoolean(a > b);
1906 case CompareGreaterEq:
1907 return jsBoolean(a >= b);
1908 case CompareEq:
1909 return jsBoolean(a == b);
1910 default:
1911 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1912 break;
1913 }
1914 };
1915 double a = leftConst.asNumber();
1916 double b = rightConst.asNumber();
1917 setConstant(node, compareNumber(a, b));
1918 break;
1919 }
1920
1921 if (leftConst.isBigInt() && rightConst.isBigInt()) {
1922 switch (node->op()) {
1923 case CompareLess:
1924 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(bigIntCompareResult(compareBigInt(leftConst, rightConst), JSBigInt::ComparisonMode::LessThan)));
1925 break;
1926 case CompareLessEq:
1927 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(bigIntCompareResult(compareBigInt(leftConst, rightConst), JSBigInt::ComparisonMode::LessThanOrEqual)));
1928 break;
1929 case CompareGreater:
1930 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(bigIntCompareResult(compareBigInt(rightConst, leftConst), JSBigInt::ComparisonMode::LessThan)));
1931 break;
1932 case CompareGreaterEq:
1933 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(bigIntCompareResult(compareBigInt(rightConst, leftConst), JSBigInt::ComparisonMode::LessThanOrEqual)));
1934 break;
1935 case CompareEq:
1936 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(compareBigInt(leftConst, rightConst) == JSBigInt::ComparisonResult::Equal));
1937 break;
1938 default:
1939 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1940 break;
1941 }
1942 break;
1943 }
1944
1945 if (leftConst.isString() && rightConst.isString()) {
1946 const StringImpl* a = asString(leftConst)->tryGetValueImpl();
1947 const StringImpl* b = asString(rightConst)->tryGetValueImpl();
1948 if (a && b) {
1949 bool result;
1950 if (node->op() == CompareEq)
1951 result = WTF::equal(a, b);
1952 else if (node->op() == CompareLess)
1953 result = codePointCompare(a, b) < 0;
1954 else if (node->op() == CompareLessEq)
1955 result = codePointCompare(a, b) <= 0;
1956 else if (node->op() == CompareGreater)
1957 result = codePointCompare(a, b) > 0;
1958 else if (node->op() == CompareGreaterEq)
1959 result = codePointCompare(a, b) >= 0;
1960 else
1961 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1962 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(result));
1963 break;
1964 }
1965 }
1966
1967 if (node->op() == CompareEq && leftConst.isSymbol() && rightConst.isSymbol()) {
1968 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(asSymbol(leftConst) == asSymbol(rightConst)));
1969 break;
1970 }
1971 }
1972
1973 if (node->op() == CompareEq) {
1974 SpeculatedType leftType = forNode(node->child1()).m_type;
1975 SpeculatedType rightType = forNode(node->child2()).m_type;
1976 if (!valuesCouldBeEqual(leftType, rightType)) {
1977 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1978 break;
1979 }
1980
1981 if (leftType == SpecOther)
1982 std::swap(leftType, rightType);
1983 if (rightType == SpecOther) {
1984 // Undefined and Null are always equal when compared to eachother.
1985 if (!(leftType & ~SpecOther)) {
1986 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
1987 break;
1988 }
1989
1990 // Any other type compared to Null or Undefined is always false
1991 // as long as the MasqueradesAsUndefined watchpoint is valid.
1992 //
1993 // MasqueradesAsUndefined only matters for SpecObjectOther, other
1994 // cases are always "false".
1995 if (!(leftType & (SpecObjectOther | SpecOther))) {
1996 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
1997 break;
1998 }
1999
2000 if (!(leftType & SpecOther) && m_graph.masqueradesAsUndefinedWatchpointIsStillValid(node->origin.semantic)) {
2001 JSGlobalObject* globalObject = m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic);
2002 m_graph.watchpoints().addLazily(globalObject->masqueradesAsUndefinedWatchpoint());
2003 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
2004 break;
2005 }
2006 }
2007 }
2008
2009 if (node->child1() == node->child2()) {
2010 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(Int32Use) ||
2011 node->isBinaryUseKind(Int52RepUse) ||
2012 node->isBinaryUseKind(BigInt32Use) ||
2013 node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse) ||
2014 node->isBinaryUseKind(AnyBigIntUse) ||
2015 node->isBinaryUseKind(StringUse) ||
2016 node->isBinaryUseKind(BooleanUse) ||
2017 node->isBinaryUseKind(SymbolUse) ||
2018 node->isBinaryUseKind(StringIdentUse) ||
2019 node->isBinaryUseKind(ObjectUse) ||
2020 node->isBinaryUseKind(ObjectUse, ObjectOrOtherUse) ||
2021 node->isBinaryUseKind(ObjectOrOtherUse, ObjectUse)) {
2022 switch (node->op()) {
2023 case CompareLess:
2024 case CompareGreater:
2025 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
2026 break;
2027 case CompareLessEq:
2028 case CompareGreaterEq:
2029 case CompareEq:
2030 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
2031 break;
2032 default:
2033 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Unexpected node type");
2034 break;
2035 }
2036 break;
2037 }
2038 }
2039
2040 if (isClobbering)
2041 clobberWorld();
2042 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
2043 break;
2044 }
2045
2046 case CompareStrictEq:
2047 case SameValue: {
2048 Node* leftNode = node->child1().node();
2049 Node* rightNode = node->child2().node();
2050 JSValue left = forNode(leftNode).value();
2051 JSValue right = forNode(rightNode).value();
2052 if (left && right) {
2053 if (left.isString() && right.isString()) {
2054 // We need this case because JSValue::strictEqual is otherwise too racy for
2055 // string comparisons.
2056 const StringImpl* a = asString(left)->tryGetValueImpl();
2057 const StringImpl* b = asString(right)->tryGetValueImpl();
2058 if (a && b) {
2059 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(WTF::equal(a, b)));
2060 break;
2061 }
2062 } else {
2063 if (node->op() == CompareStrictEq)
2064 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(JSValue::strictEqual(nullptr, left, right)));
2065 else
2066 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(sameValue(nullptr, left, right)));
2067 break;
2068 }
2069 }
2070
2071 // FIXME: why is this check here, and not later (after the type-based replacement by false).
2072 // Saam seems to agree that the two checks could be switched, I'll try that in a separate patch
2073 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse)) {
2074 auto isNonStringAndNonBigIntCellConstant = [] (JSValue value) {
2075 return value && value.isCell() && !value.isString() && !value.isHeapBigInt();
2076 };
2077
2078 if (isNonStringAndNonBigIntCellConstant(left) || isNonStringAndNonBigIntCellConstant(right)) {
2079 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
2080 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
2081 break;
2082 }
2083 }
2084
2085 SpeculatedType leftLUB = leastUpperBoundOfStrictlyEquivalentSpeculations(forNode(leftNode).m_type);
2086 SpeculatedType rightLUB = leastUpperBoundOfStrictlyEquivalentSpeculations(forNode(rightNode).m_type);
2087 if (!(leftLUB & rightLUB)) {
2088 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
2089 break;
2090 }
2091
2092 if (node->child1() == node->child2()) {
2093 // FIXME: Is there any case not involving NaN where x === x is not guaranteed to return true?
2094 // If not I might slightly simplify that check.
2095 if (node->isBinaryUseKind(BooleanUse)
2096 || node->isBinaryUseKind(Int32Use)
2097 || node->isBinaryUseKind(Int52RepUse)
2098 || node->isBinaryUseKind(StringUse)
2099 || node->isBinaryUseKind(StringIdentUse)
2100 || node->isBinaryUseKind(SymbolUse)
2101 || node->isBinaryUseKind(ObjectUse)
2102 || node->isBinaryUseKind(MiscUse, UntypedUse)
2103 || node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse, MiscUse)
2104 || node->isBinaryUseKind(StringIdentUse, NotStringVarUse)
2105 || node->isBinaryUseKind(NotStringVarUse, StringIdentUse)
2106 || node->isBinaryUseKind(StringUse, UntypedUse)
2107 || node->isBinaryUseKind(UntypedUse, StringUse)
2108 || node->isBinaryUseKind(BigInt32Use)
2109 || node->isBinaryUseKind(HeapBigIntUse)
2110 || node->isBinaryUseKind(AnyBigIntUse)) {
2111 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
2112 break;
2113 }
2114 }
2115
2116 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
2117 break;
2118 }
2119
2120 case CompareEqPtr: {
2121 Node* childNode = node->child1().node();
2122 JSValue childValue = forNode(childNode).value();
2123 if (childValue) {
2124 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(childValue.isCell() && childValue.asCell() == node->cellOperand()->cell()));
2125 break;
2126 }
2127
2128 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
2129 break;
2130 }
2131
2132 case StringCharCodeAt:
2133 case StringCodePointAt:

2165 if (node->op() == GetByVal) {
2166 auto foldGetByValOnConstantProperty = [&] (Edge& arrayEdge, Edge& indexEdge) {
2167 // FIXME: We can expand this for non x86 environments.
2168 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=134641
2169 if (!isX86())
2170 return false;
2171
2172 AbstractValue& arrayValue = forNode(arrayEdge);
2173
2174 // Check the structure set is finite. This means that this constant's structure is watched and guaranteed the one of this set.
2175 // When the structure is changed, this code should be invalidated. This is important since the following code relies on the
2176 // constant object's is not changed.
2177 if (!arrayValue.m_structure.isFinite())
2178 return false;
2179
2180 JSValue arrayConstant = arrayValue.value();
2181 if (!arrayConstant)
2182 return false;
2183
2184 JSObject* array = jsDynamicCast<JSObject*>(m_vm, arrayConstant);
2185 if (!array)
2186 return false;
2187
2188 JSValue indexConstant = forNode(indexEdge).value();
2189 if (!indexConstant || !indexConstant.isInt32() || indexConstant.asInt32() < 0)
2190 return false;
2191 uint32_t index = indexConstant.asUInt32();
2192
2193 // Check that the early StructureID is not nuked, get the butterfly, and check the late StructureID again.
2194 // And we check the indexing mode of the structure. If the indexing mode is CoW, the butterfly is
2195 // definitely JSImmutableButterfly.
2196 StructureID structureIDEarly = array->structureID();
2197 if (isNuked(structureIDEarly))
2198 return false;
2199
2200 if (node->arrayMode().arrayClass() == Array::OriginalCopyOnWriteArray) {
2201
2202 WTF::loadLoadFence();
2203 Butterfly* butterfly = array->butterfly();
2204
2205 WTF::loadLoadFence();
2206 StructureID structureIDLate = array->structureID();
2207
2208 if (structureIDEarly != structureIDLate)
2209 return false;
2210
2211 Structure* structure = m_vm.getStructure(structureIDLate);
2212 switch (node->arrayMode().type()) {
2213 case Array::Int32:
2214 case Array::Contiguous:
2215 case Array::Double:
2216 if (structure->indexingMode() != (toIndexingShape(node->arrayMode().type()) | CopyOnWrite | IsArray))
2217 return false;
2218 break;
2219 default:
2220 return false;
2221 }
2222 ASSERT(isCopyOnWrite(structure->indexingMode()));
2223
2224 JSImmutableButterfly* immutableButterfly = JSImmutableButterfly::fromButterfly(butterfly);
2225 if (index < immutableButterfly->length()) {
2226 JSValue value = immutableButterfly->get(index);
2227 ASSERT(value);
2228 if (value.isCell())
2229 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(value.asCell()));
2230 else
2231 setConstant(node, value);
2232 return true;
2233 }
2234
2235 if (node->arrayMode().isOutOfBounds()) {
2236 JSGlobalObject* globalObject = m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic);
2237 Structure* arrayPrototypeStructure = globalObject->arrayPrototype()->structure(m_vm);
2238 Structure* objectPrototypeStructure = globalObject->objectPrototype()->structure(m_vm);
2239 if (arrayPrototypeStructure->transitionWatchpointSetIsStillValid()
2240 && objectPrototypeStructure->transitionWatchpointSetIsStillValid()
2241 && globalObject->arrayPrototypeChainIsSane()) {
2242 m_graph.registerAndWatchStructureTransition(arrayPrototypeStructure);
2243 m_graph.registerAndWatchStructureTransition(objectPrototypeStructure);
2244 if (node->arrayMode().type() == Array::Double && node->arrayMode().isOutOfBoundsSaneChain() && !(node->flags() & NodeBytecodeUsesAsOther))
2245 setConstant(node, jsNumber(PNaN));
2246 else
2247 setConstant(node, jsUndefined());
2248 return true;
2249 }
2250 }
2251 return false;
2252 }
2253
2254 if (node->arrayMode().type() == Array::ArrayStorage || node->arrayMode().type() == Array::SlowPutArrayStorage) {
2255 JSValue value;
2256 {
2257 // ArrayStorage's Butterfly can be half-broken state.
2258 Locker locker { array->cellLock() };
2259
2260 WTF::loadLoadFence();
2261 Butterfly* butterfly = array->butterfly();
2262
2263 WTF::loadLoadFence();
2264 StructureID structureIDLate = array->structureID();
2265
2266 if (structureIDEarly != structureIDLate)
2267 return false;
2268
2269 Structure* structure = m_vm.getStructure(structureIDLate);
2270 if (!hasAnyArrayStorage(structure->indexingMode()))
2271 return false;
2272
2273 if (structure->typeInfo().interceptsGetOwnPropertySlotByIndexEvenWhenLengthIsNotZero())
2274 return false;
2275
2276 ArrayStorage* storage = butterfly->arrayStorage();
2277 if (index >= storage->length())
2278 return false;
2279
2280 if (index < storage->vectorLength())
2281 return false;
2282
2283 SparseArrayValueMap* map = storage->m_sparseMap.get();
2284 if (!map)
2285 return false;
2286
2287 value = map->getConcurrently(index);
2288 }
2289 if (!value)
2290 return false;
2291
2292 if (value.isCell())
2293 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(value.asCell()));
2294 else
2295 setConstant(node, value);
2296 return true;
2297 }
2298
2299 return false;
2300 };

2332 // The returned value from Atomics.store does not rely on typed array types. It is relying
2333 // on input's UseKind. For example,
2334 //
2335 // Atomics.store(uint8Array, /* index */ 0, Infinity) // => returned value is Infinity
2336 //
2337 // Since the other ReadModifyWrite atomics return values stored in the typed array previously,
2338 // the returned values rely on the typed array types. On the other hand, Atomics.store's
2339 // returned value is input value. This means that Atomics.store + Uint8Array can return doubles
2340 // while the typed array is Uint8Array (the above one is the example).

3546 }
3547 m_state.setIsValid(false);
3548 break;

3552 bool allGood = true;
3553 m_phiChildren->forAllTransitiveIncomingValues(
3554 node,

3556 if (Structure* structure = incoming->dynamicCastConstant<Structure*>(m_vm)) {
3557 if (set.contains(m_graph.registerStructure(structure)))
3558 return;
3559 }
3560 allGood = false;
3561 });
3562 if (allGood) {
3563 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3564 break;
3565 }
3566 }

3568 if (RegisteredStructure structure = set.onlyStructure()) {
3569 filterByValue(node->child1(), *m_graph.freeze(structure.get()));
3570 break;
3571 }

3573 // Aw shucks, we can't do anything!
3574 break;
3575 }

3577 case PutStructure:

3579 if (forNode(node->child1()).m_structure.onlyStructure() == node->transition()->next) {
3580 didFoldClobberStructures();
3581 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3582 } else {
3583 observeTransition(
3584 clobberLimit, node->transition()->previous, node->transition()->next);
3585 forNode(node->child1()).changeStructure(m_graph, node->transition()->next);
3586 }
3587 } else {
3588 // We're going to exit before we get here, but for the sake of validation, we've folded our write to StructureID.
3589 didFoldClobberStructures();
3590 }
3591 break;
3592 case GetButterfly:
3593 case AllocatePropertyStorage:
3594 case ReallocatePropertyStorage:
3595 case NukeStructureAndSetButterfly:
3596 // FIXME: We don't model the fact that the structureID is nuked, simply because currently
3597 // nobody would currently benefit from having that information. But it's a bug nonetheless.
3598 if (node->op() == NukeStructureAndSetButterfly)
3599 didFoldClobberStructures();
3600 clearForNode(node); // The result is not a JS value.
3601 break;
3602 case CheckJSCast: {
3603 const ClassInfo* classInfo = node->classInfo();

3605 if (constant) {

3609 ASSERT(constant);
3610 break;
3611 }
3612 }
3613

3615
3616 if (value.m_structure.isSubClassOf(classInfo))
3617 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3618
3619 filterClassInfo(value, classInfo);
3620 break;
3621 }

3627 ASSERT(!classInfo->inheritsJSTypeRange || !classInfo->inheritsJSTypeRange->contains(constant.asCell()->type()));
3628 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3629 ASSERT(constant);

3635
3636 if (value.m_structure.isNotSubClassOf(classInfo))
3637 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);

3739 case Arrayify: {
3740 if (node->arrayMode().alreadyChecked(m_graph, node, forNode(node->child1()))) {
3741 didFoldClobberStructures();

3743 break;

3750 case ArrayifyToStructure: {
3751 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
3752 if (value.m_structure.isSubsetOf(RegisteredStructureSet(node->structure())))
3753 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3754 clobberStructures();
3755
3756 // We have a bunch of options of how to express the abstract set at this point. Let set S
3757 // be the set of structures that the value had before clobbering and assume that all of
3758 // them are watchable. The new value should be the least expressible upper bound of the
3759 // intersection of "values that currently have structure = node->structure()" and "values
3760 // that have structure in S plus any structure transition-reachable from S". Assume that
3761 // node->structure() is not in S but it is transition-reachable from S. Then we would
3762 // like to say that the result is "values that have structure = node->structure() until
3763 // we invalidate", but there is no way to express this using the AbstractValue syntax. So
3764 // we must choose between:
3765 //
3766 // 1) "values that currently have structure = node->structure()". This is a valid
3767 // superset of the value that we really want, and it's specific enough to satisfy the
3768 // preconditions of the array access that this is guarding. It's also specific enough
3769 // to allow relevant optimizations in the case that we didn't have a contradiction
3770 // like in this example. Notice that in the abscence of any contradiction, this result
3771 // is precise rather than being a conservative LUB.
3772 //
3773 // 2) "values that currently hava structure in S plus any structure transition-reachable
3774 // from S". This is also a valid superset of the value that we really want, but it's
3775 // not specific enough to satisfy the preconditions of the array access that this is
3776 // guarding - so playing such shenanigans would preclude us from having assertions on
3777 // the typing preconditions of any array accesses. This would also not be a desirable
3778 // answer in the absence of a contradiction.
3779 //
3780 // Note that it's tempting to simply say that the resulting value is BOTTOM because of
3781 // the contradiction. That would be wrong, since we haven't hit an invalidation point,
3782 // yet.
3783 forNode(node->child1()).set(m_graph, node->structure());
3784 break;
3785 }
3786 case GetIndexedPropertyStorage: {
3787 JSArrayBufferView* view = m_graph.tryGetFoldableView(
3788 forNode(node->child1()).m_value, node->arrayMode());
3789 if (view)
3790 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3791 clearForNode(node);
3792 break;
3793 }
3794 case ConstantStoragePointer: {
3795 clearForNode(node);
3796 break;
3797 }
3798
3799 case GetTypedArrayByteOffset: {
3800 JSArrayBufferView* view = m_graph.tryGetFoldableView(forNode(node->child1()).m_value);
3801 if (view) {
3802 std::optional<unsigned> byteOffset = view->byteOffsetConcurrently();
3803 if (byteOffset) {
3804 setConstant(node, jsNumber(*byteOffset));
3805 break;
3806 }
3807 }
3808 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
3809 break;

3812 case GetPrototypeOf: {
3813 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
3814 if ((value.m_type && !(value.m_type & ~SpecObject)) && value.m_structure.isFinite()) {
3815 bool canFold = !value.m_structure.isClear();
3816 JSValue prototype;
3817 value.m_structure.forEach([&] (RegisteredStructure structure) {
3818 if (structure->typeInfo().overridesGetPrototype()) {
3819 canFold = false;
3820 return;
3821 }
3822
3823 if (structure->hasPolyProto()) {
3824 canFold = false;
3825 return;
3826 }
3827 if (!prototype)
3828 prototype = structure->storedPrototype();
3829 else if (prototype != structure->storedPrototype())
3830 canFold = false;
3831 });
3832
3833 if (prototype && canFold) {
3834 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
3835 case ArrayUse:
3836 case FunctionUse:
3837 case FinalObjectUse:
3838 break;
3839 default:
3840 didFoldClobberWorld();
3841 break;
3842 }
3843 setConstant(node, *m_graph.freeze(prototype));
3844 break;
3845 }
3846 }
3847
3848 switch (node->child1().useKind()) {
3849 case ArrayUse:
3850 case FunctionUse:
3851 case FinalObjectUse:
3852 break;
3853 default:
3854 clobberWorld();
3855 break;
3856 }
3857 setTypeForNode(node, SpecObject | SpecOther);
3858 break;

3861 case GetByOffset: {
3862 StorageAccessData& data = node->storageAccessData();
3863
3864 // FIXME: The part of this that handles inferred property types relies on AI knowing the structure
3865 // right now. That's probably not optimal. In some cases, we may perform an optimization (usually
3866 // by something other than AI, maybe by CSE for example) that obscures AI's view of the structure
3867 // at the point where GetByOffset runs. Currently, when that happens, we'll have to rely entirely
3868 // on the type that ByteCodeParser was able to prove.
3869 AbstractValue value = m_graph.inferredValueForProperty(

3873 // because the compilation was already invalidated.

3896 case MultiGetByOffset: {
3897 // This code will filter the base value in a manner that is possibly different (either more
3898 // or less precise) than the way it would be filtered if this was strength-reduced to a
3899 // CheckStructure. This is fine. It's legal for different passes over the code to prove
3900 // different things about the code, so long as all of them are sound. That even includes
3901 // one guy proving that code should never execute (due to a contradiction) and another guy
3902 // not finding that contradiction. If someone ever proved that there would be a
3903 // contradiction then there must always be a contradiction even if subsequent passes don't
3904 // realize it. This is the case here.
3905
3906 // Ordinarily you have to be careful with calling setShouldTryConstantFolding()
3907 // because of the effect on compile times, but this node is FTL-only.
3908 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3909
3910 AbstractValue base = forNode(node->child1());
3911 RegisteredStructureSet baseSet;
3912 AbstractValue result;
3913 for (const MultiGetByOffsetCase& getCase : node->multiGetByOffsetData().cases) {
3914 RegisteredStructureSet set = getCase.set();
3915 set.filter(base);
3916 if (set.isEmpty())
3917 continue;
3918 baseSet.merge(set);
3919
3920 switch (getCase.method().kind()) {
3921 case GetByOffsetMethod::Constant: {
3922 AbstractValue thisResult;
3923 thisResult.set(
3924 m_graph,
3925 *getCase.method().constant(),
3926 m_state.structureClobberState());
3927 result.merge(thisResult);
3928 break;
3929 }
3930
3931 default: {
3932 result.makeHeapTop();
3933 break;
3934 } }
3935 }
3936
3937 if (forNode(node->child1()).changeStructure(m_graph, baseSet) == Contradiction)
3938 m_state.setIsValid(false);
3939
3940 setForNode(node, result);
3941 break;
3942 }
3943
3944 case PutByOffset: {
3945 break;
3946 }
