3948 case MultiPutByOffset: {
3949 RegisteredStructureSet newSet;
3950 TransitionVector transitions;
3951
3952 // Ordinarily you have to be careful with calling setShouldTryConstantFolding()
3953 // because of the effect on compile times, but this node is FTL-only.
3954 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
3955
3956 AbstractValue base = forNode(node->child1());
3957 AbstractValue originalValue = forNode(node->child2());
3958 AbstractValue resultingValue;
3959
3960 if (node->multiPutByOffsetData().writesStructures())
3961 didFoldClobberStructures();
3962
3963 for (unsigned i = node->multiPutByOffsetData().variants.size(); i--;) {
3964 const PutByIdVariant& variant = node->multiPutByOffsetData().variants[i];
3965 RegisteredStructureSet thisSet = *m_graph.addStructureSet(variant.oldStructure());
3966 thisSet.filter(base);
3967 if (thisSet.isEmpty())
3968 continue;
3969
3970 AbstractValue thisValue = originalValue;
3971 resultingValue.merge(thisValue);
3972
3973 if (variant.kind() == PutByIdVariant::Transition) {
3974 RegisteredStructure newStructure = m_graph.registerStructure(variant.newStructure());
3975 if (thisSet.onlyStructure() != newStructure) {
3976 transitions.append(
3977 Transition(m_graph.registerStructure(variant.oldStructureForTransition()), newStructure));
3978 } // else this is really a replace.
3979 newSet.add(newStructure);
3980 } else {
3981 ASSERT(variant.kind() == PutByIdVariant::Replace);
3982 newSet.merge(thisSet);
3983 }
3984 }
3985
3986 // We need to order AI executing these effects in the same order as they're executed
3987 // at runtime. This is critical when you have JS code like `o.f = o;`. We first
3988 // filter types on o, then transition o. Not the other way around. If we got
3989 // this ordering wrong, we could end up with the wrong type representing o.
3990 setForNode(node->child2(), resultingValue);
3991 if (!!originalValue && !resultingValue)
3992 m_state.setIsValid(false);
3993
3994 observeTransitions(clobberLimit, transitions);
3995 if (forNode(node->child1()).changeStructure(m_graph, newSet) == Contradiction)
3996 m_state.setIsValid(false);
3997 break;
3998 }

4104 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);

4108 // to us just do that to maintain the invariant that they can't be hoisted higher than us.

4110 // thing to do here. We pick NodeResultJS because it makes converting this to an identity

4130 auto privateFieldPutKind = node->op() == PutPrivateNameById ? node->privateFieldPutKind() : PrivateFieldPutKind::none();
4131 PutByIdStatus status = PutByIdStatus::computeFor(

4172 m_state.setIsValid(false);
4173 break;

4226 }

4228 case HasPrivateName:
4229 case HasPrivateBrand: {
4230 clobberWorld();
4231 filter(node->child1(), SpecObject);
4232 filter(node->child2(), SpecSymbol);
4233 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4234 break;
4235 }
4236
4237 case HasOwnProperty: {
4238 clobberWorld();
4239 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4240 break;
4241 }
4242
4243 case GetEnumerableLength: {
4244 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
4245 break;
4246 }
4247 case HasEnumerableProperty: {
4248 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4249 clobberWorld();
4250 break;
4251 }
4252 case InStructureProperty:
4253 case HasOwnStructureProperty:
4254 case HasEnumerableStructureProperty: {
4255 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4256 clobberWorld();
4257 break;
4258 }
4259 case HasIndexedProperty:
4260 case HasEnumerableIndexedProperty: {
4261 ArrayMode mode = node->arrayMode();
4262 switch (mode.type()) {
4263 case Array::Int32:
4264 case Array::Double:
4265 case Array::Contiguous:
4266 case Array::ArrayStorage: {
4267 if (mode.isInBounds())
4268 break;
4269 FALLTHROUGH;
4270 }
4271 default: {
4272 clobberWorld();
4273 break;
4274 }
4275 }
4276 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4277 break;
4278 }
4279 case GetDirectPname: {
4280 clobberWorld();
4281 makeHeapTopForNode(node);
4282 break;
4283 }
4284 case GetPropertyEnumerator: {
4285 setTypeForNode(node, SpecCell);
4286 clobberWorld();
4287 break;
4288 }
4289 case GetEnumeratorStructurePname: {
4290 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString | SpecOther);
4291 break;
4292 }
4293 case GetEnumeratorGenericPname: {
4294 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString | SpecOther);
4295 break;
4296 }
4297 case ToIndexString: {
4298 setTypeForNode(node, SpecString);
4299 break;
4300 }
4301
4302 case GetGlobalVar:
4303 makeHeapTopForNode(node);
4304 break;
4305
4306 case GetGlobalLexicalVariable:
4307 makeBytecodeTopForNode(node);
4308 break;
4309
4310 case GetDynamicVar:
4311 clobberWorld();
4312 makeBytecodeTopForNode(node);
4313 break;
4314
4315 case PutDynamicVar:
4316 clobberWorld();
4317 break;
4318
4319 case ResolveScope:
4320 clobberWorld();
4321 setTypeForNode(node, SpecObject);
4322 break;
4323
4324 case ResolveScopeForHoistingFuncDeclInEval:
4325 clobberWorld();
4326 makeBytecodeTopForNode(node);
4327 break;
4328
4329 case PutGlobalVariable:
4330 case NotifyWrite:
4331 break;
4332
4333 case OverridesHasInstance:
4334 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4335 break;
4336
4337 case InstanceOf:
4338 clobberWorld();
4339 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4340 break;
4341
4342 case InstanceOfCustom:
4343 clobberWorld();
4344 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4345 break;
4346
4347 case MatchStructure: {
4348 AbstractValue base = forNode(node->child1());
4349 RegisteredStructureSet baseSet;
4350
4351 BooleanLattice result = BooleanLattice::Bottom;
4352 for (MatchStructureVariant& variant : node->matchStructureData().variants) {
4353 RegisteredStructure structure = variant.structure;
4354 if (!base.contains(structure)) {
4355 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4356 continue;
4357 }
4358
4359 baseSet.add(structure);
4360 result = leastUpperBoundOfBooleanLattices(
4361 result, variant.result ? BooleanLattice::True : BooleanLattice::False);
4362 }
4363
4364 if (forNode(node->child1()).changeStructure(m_graph, baseSet) == Contradiction)
4365 m_state.setIsValid(false);
4366
4367 switch (result) {
4368 case BooleanLattice::False:
4369 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(false));
4370 break;
4371 case BooleanLattice::True:
4372 setConstant(node, jsBoolean(true));
4373 break;
4374 default:
4375 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBoolean);
4376 break;
4377 }
4378 break;
4379 }
4380
4381 case Phi:
4382 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_graph.m_form == SSA);
4383 setForNode(node, forNode(NodeFlowProjection(node, NodeFlowProjection::Shadow)));
4384 // The state of this node would have already been decided, but it may have become a
4385 // constant, in which case we'd like to know.
4386 if (forNode(node).m_value)
4387 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4388 break;
4389
4390 case Upsilon: {
4391 NodeFlowProjection shadow(node->phi(), NodeFlowProjection::Shadow);
4392 if (shadow.isStillValid()) {
4393 m_state.createValueForNode(shadow);
4394 setForNode(shadow, forNode(node->child1()));
4395 }
4396 break;
4397 }
4398
4399 case Flush:
4400 case PhantomLocal:
4401 break;
4402
4403 case Call:
4404 case TailCallInlinedCaller:
4405 case Construct:
4406 case CallVarargs:
4407 case CallForwardVarargs:
4408 case TailCallVarargsInlinedCaller:
4409 case ConstructVarargs:
4410 case ConstructForwardVarargs:
4411 case TailCallForwardVarargsInlinedCaller:
4412 case CallEval:
4413 case DirectCall:
4414 case DirectConstruct:
4415 case DirectTailCallInlinedCaller:
4416 clobberWorld();
4417 makeHeapTopForNode(node);
4418 break;
4419
4420 case ForceOSRExit:
4421 case CheckBadValue:
4422 m_state.setIsValid(false);
4423 break;
4424
4425 case InvalidationPoint:
4426 m_state.setStructureClobberState(StructuresAreWatched);
4427 m_state.observeInvalidationPoint();
4428 break;
4429
4430 case CPUIntrinsic:
4431 if (node->intrinsic() == CPURdtscIntrinsic)
4432 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
4433 else
4434 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecOther);
4435 break;
4436
4437 case CheckTraps:
4438 case LogShadowChickenPrologue:
4439 case LogShadowChickenTail:
4440 case ProfileType:
4441 case ProfileControlFlow:
4442 case Phantom:
4443 case CountExecution:
4444 case CheckTierUpInLoop:
4445 case CheckTierUpAtReturn:
4446 case CheckDetached:
4447 case SuperSamplerBegin:
4448 case SuperSamplerEnd:
4449 case CheckTierUpAndOSREnter:
4450 case LoopHint:
4451 case ExitOK:
4452 case FilterCallLinkStatus:
4453 case FilterGetByStatus:
4454 case FilterPutByIdStatus:
4455 case FilterInByStatus:
4456 case FilterDeleteByStatus:
4457 case FilterCheckPrivateBrandStatus:
4458 case FilterSetPrivateBrandStatus:
4459 case ClearCatchLocals:
4460 break;
4461
4462 case CheckTypeInfoFlags: {
4463 const AbstractValue& abstractValue = forNode(node->child1());
4464 unsigned bits = node->typeInfoOperand();
4465 ASSERT(bits);
4466 if (bits == ImplementsDefaultHasInstance) {
4467 if (abstractValue.m_type == SpecFunctionWithDefaultHasInstance) {
4468 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4469 break;
4470 }
4471 }
4472
4473 if (JSValue value = abstractValue.value()) {
4474 if (value.isCell()) {
4475 // This works because if we see a cell here, we know it's fully constructed
4476 // and we can read its inline type info flags. These flags don't change over the
4477 // object's lifetime.
4478 if ((value.asCell()->inlineTypeFlags() & bits) == bits) {
4479 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4480 break;
4481 }
4482 }
4483 }
4484
4485 if (abstractValue.m_structure.isFinite()) {
4486 bool ok = true;
4487 abstractValue.m_structure.forEach([&] (RegisteredStructure structure) {
4488 ok &= (structure->typeInfo().inlineTypeFlags() & bits) == bits;
4489 });
4490 if (ok) {
4491 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4492 break;
4493 }
4494 }
4495
4496 break;
4497 }
4498
4499 case ParseInt: {
4500 AbstractValue value = forNode(node->child1());
4501 if (value.m_type && !(value.m_type & ~SpecInt32Only)) {
4502 JSValue radix;
4503 if (!node->child2())
4504 radix = jsNumber(0);
4505 else
4506 radix = forNode(node->child2()).m_value;
4507
4508 if (radix.isNumber()
4509 && (radix.asNumber() == 0 || radix.asNumber() == 10)) {
4510 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4511 if (node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse)
4512 didFoldClobberWorld();
4513 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
4514 break;
4515 }
4516 }
4517
4518 if (node->child1().useKind() == UntypedUse)
4519 clobberWorld();
4520 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecBytecodeNumber);
4521 break;
4522 }
4523
4524 case CreateRest:
4525 if (!m_graph.isWatchingHavingABadTimeWatchpoint(node)) {
4526 // This means we're already having a bad time.
4527 clobberWorld();
4528 setTypeForNode(node, SpecArray);
4529 break;
4530 }
4531 setForNode(node,
4532 m_graph.globalObjectFor(node->origin.semantic)->restParameterStructure());
4533 break;
4534
4535 case CheckVarargs:
4536 case Check: {
4537 // Simplify out checks that don't actually do checking.
4538 m_graph.doToChildren(node, [&] (Edge edge) {
4539 if (!edge)
4540 return;
4541 if (edge.isProved() || edge.willNotHaveCheck())
4542 m_state.setShouldTryConstantFolding(true);
4543 });
4544 break;
4545 }
4546
4547 case SetFunctionName: {
4548 clobberWorld();
4549 break;
4550 }
4551
4552 case StoreBarrier:
4553 case FencedStoreBarrier: {
4554 filter(node->child1(), SpecCell);
4555 break;
4556 }
4557
4558 case DataViewGetInt: {
4559 DataViewData data = node->dataViewData();
4560 if (data.byteSize < 4)
4561 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
4562 else {
4563 ASSERT(data.byteSize == 4);
4564 if (data.isSigned)
4565 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only);
4566 else
4567 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt52Any);
4568 }
4569 break;
4570 }
4571
4572 case DataViewGetFloat: {
4573 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecFullDouble);
4574 break;
4575 }
4576
4577 case DateGetInt32OrNaN: {
4578 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecInt32Only | SpecDoublePureNaN);
4579 break;
4580 }
4581
4582 case DateGetTime: {
4583 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, SpecFullDouble);
4584 break;
4585 }
4586
4587 case DataViewSet: {
4588 break;
4589 }
4590
4591 case Unreachable:
4592 // It may be that during a previous run of AI we proved that something was unreachable, but
4593 // during this run of AI we forget that it's unreachable. AI's proofs don't have to get
4594 // monotonically stronger over time. So, we don't assert that AI doesn't reach the
4595 // Unreachable. We have no choice but to take our past proof at face value. Otherwise we'll
4596 // crash whenever AI fails to be as powerful on run K as it was on run K-1.
4597 m_state.setIsValid(false);
4598 break;
4599
4600 case LastNodeType:
4601 case ArithIMul:
4602 case FiatInt52:
4603 DFG_CRASH(m_graph, node, "Unexpected node type");
4604 break;
4605 }
4606
4607 return m_state.isValid();
4608}

4610template<typename AbstractStateType>
4611void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::filterICStatus(Node* node)
4612{
4613 switch (node->op()) {
4614 case FilterCallLinkStatus:
4615 if (JSValue value = forNode(node->child1()).m_value)
4616 node->callLinkStatus()->filter(m_vm, value);
4617 break;
4618
4619 case FilterGetByStatus: {
4620 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4621 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4622 node->getByStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4623 break;
4624 }
4625
4626 case FilterInByStatus: {
4627 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4628 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4629 node->inByStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4630 break;
4631 }
4632
4633 case FilterPutByIdStatus: {
4634 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4635 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4636 node->putByIdStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4637 break;
4638 }
4639
4640 case FilterDeleteByStatus: {
4641 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4642 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4643 node->deleteByStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4644 break;
4645 }
4646
4647 case FilterCheckPrivateBrandStatus: {
4648 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4649 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4650 node->checkPrivateBrandStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4651 break;
4652 }
4653
4654 case FilterSetPrivateBrandStatus: {
4655 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node->child1());
4656 if (value.m_structure.isFinite())
4657 node->setPrivateBrandStatus()->filter(value.m_structure.toStructureSet());
4658 break;
4659 }
4660
4661
4662 default:
4663 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4664 break;
4665 }

4704template<typename AbstractStateType>
4705template<typename Functor>
4706void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::forAllValues(
4707 unsigned clobberLimit, Functor& functor)
4708{
4709 if (clobberLimit >= m_state.block()->size())
4710 clobberLimit = m_state.block()->size();
4711 else
4712 clobberLimit++;
4713 ASSERT(clobberLimit <= m_state.block()->size());
4714 for (size_t i = clobberLimit; i--;) {
4715 NodeFlowProjection::forEach(
4716 m_state.block()->at(i),
4717 [&] (NodeFlowProjection nodeProjection) {
4718 functor(forNode(nodeProjection));
4719 });
4720 }
4721 if (m_graph.m_form == SSA) {
4722 for (NodeFlowProjection node : m_state.block()->ssa->liveAtHead) {
4723 if (node.isStillValid())
4724 functor(forNode(node));
4725 }
4726 }
4727 for (size_t i = m_state.size(); i--;)
4728 functor(m_state.atIndex(i));
4729}

4736 m_state.setStructureClobberState(StructuresAreClobbered);
4737}

4745template<typename AbstractStateType>
4746void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::observeTransition(
4747 unsigned clobberLimit, RegisteredStructure from, RegisteredStructure to)
4748{
4749 // Stop performing precise structure transition tracking.
4750 // Precise structure transition tracking shows quadratic complexity for # of nodes in a basic block.
4751 // If it is too large, we conservatively clobber all the structures.
4752 if (m_state.block()->size() > Options::maxDFGNodesInBasicBlockForPreciseAnalysis()) {
4753 clobberStructures();
4754 return;
4755 }
4756
4757 AbstractValue::TransitionObserver transitionObserver(from, to);
4758 forAllValues(clobberLimit, transitionObserver);
4759
4760 ASSERT(!from->dfgShouldWatch()); // We don't need to claim to be in a clobbered state because 'from' was never watchable (during the time we were compiling), hence no constants ever introduced into the DFG IR that ever had a watchable structure would ever have the same structure as from.
4761
4762 m_state.mergeClobberState(AbstractInterpreterClobberState::ObservedTransitions);
4763}
4764
4765template<typename AbstractStateType>
4766void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::observeTransitions(
4767 unsigned clobberLimit, const TransitionVector& vector)
4768{
4769 if (vector.isEmpty())
4770 return;
4771
4772 // Stop performing precise structure transition tracking.
4773 // Precise structure transition tracking shows quadratic complexity for # of nodes in a basic block.
4774 // If it is too large, we conservatively clobber all the structures.
4775 if (m_state.block()->size() > Options::maxDFGNodesInBasicBlockForPreciseAnalysis()) {
4776 clobberStructures();
4777 return;
4778 }
4779
4780 AbstractValue::TransitionsObserver transitionsObserver(vector);
4781 forAllValues(clobberLimit, transitionsObserver);
4782
4783 if (ASSERT_ENABLED) {
4784 // We don't need to claim to be in a clobbered state because none of the Transition::previous structures are watchable.
4785 for (unsigned i = vector.size(); i--;)
4786 ASSERT(!vector[i].previous->dfgShouldWatch());
4787 }
4788
4789 m_state.mergeClobberState(AbstractInterpreterClobberState::ObservedTransitions);
4790}

4798template<typename AbstractStateType>
4799void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::dump(PrintStream& out)
4800{
4801 CommaPrinter comma(" ");
4802 HashSet<NodeFlowProjection> seen;
4803 if (m_graph.m_form == SSA) {
4804 for (NodeFlowProjection node : m_state.block()->ssa->liveAtHead) {
4805 seen.add(node);
4806 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node);
4807 if (value.isClear())
4808 continue;
4809 out.print(comma, node, ":", value);
4810 }
4811 }
4812 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_state.block()->size(); ++i) {
4813 NodeFlowProjection::forEach(
4814 m_state.block()->at(i), [&] (NodeFlowProjection nodeProjection) {
4815 seen.add(nodeProjection);
4816 AbstractValue& value = forNode(nodeProjection);
4817 if (value.isClear())
4818 return;
4819 out.print(comma, nodeProjection, ":", value);
4820 });
4821 }
4822 if (m_graph.m_form == SSA) {
4823 for (NodeFlowProjection node : m_state.block()->ssa->liveAtTail) {
4824 if (seen.contains(node))
4825 continue;
4826 AbstractValue& value = forNode(node);
4827 if (value.isClear())
4828 continue;
4829 out.print(comma, node, ":", value);
4830 }
4831 }
4832}

4884template<typename AbstractStateType>
4885void AbstractInterpreter<AbstractStateType>::executeDoubleUnaryOpEffects(Node* node, double(*equivalentFunction)(double))
4886{
4887 JSValue child = forNode(node->child1()).value();
4888 if (std::optional<double> number = child.toNumberFromPrimitive()) {
4889 if (node->child1().useKind() != DoubleRepUse)
4890 didFoldClobberWorld();
4891 setConstant(node, jsDoubleNumber(equivalentFunction(*number)));
4892 return;
4893 }
4894 SpeculatedType type;
4895 if (node->child1().useKind() == DoubleRepUse)
4896 type = typeOfDoubleUnaryOp(forNode(node->child1()).m_type);
4897 else {
4898 clobberWorld();
4899 type = SpecBytecodeNumber;
4900 }
4901 setNonCellTypeForNode(node, type);
4902}
